          "description": "Im in this outpatient waiting room right now and just witnessed some security guard bothering this woman for sleeping on one of the couches in the waiting room. This woman has probably (like me) been here since before 6am.\nThere are no signs that or mentions in their posted waiting room policy that say otherwise. There are plenty of seats and the woman was bothering no one.\nThis person has nothing better to do than bug this woman?\nIt is my understanding as an earthling that people sometimes sleep in hospital waiting rooms when family members are undergoing procedures, especially early.\nIf i trained security people there, I would tell them not to hassle family members for petty reasons. They don't know the nature of the situation surrounding the surgeries. Terrible",
