          "description": "I had physical therapy at this location. I was going to cancel my future appointments at this location but I really like my physical therapist and plus I need the therapy. They push you to use the kiosk which is fine. There is a person standing at the entry way to help you. I asked the rude lady for help because I had cash. She huffed and puffed a little bit so when she huffed and puffed then I got annoyed. I tried to explain to her that I have cash but I do have an old debit card on file that I would like to update.  Once she sucked her teeth she got on my nerves. So she tapped for the old debit card for the payment. If it wasn\u2019t for my physical therapist I would not be returning to this location because of Laticia\u2019s nasty attitude. While I am sitting waiting to be called the lady at the front with the burgundy braids / dreads was just as nasty to two other patients. I don\u2019t understand why people apply for jobs dealing with patients and then they have these unprofessional attitudes! I\u2019m sure they put on an act during their interview process. The other ladies at the front desk have always been professional and pleasant! So if you have to deal with Laticia or that other lady at the desk Good Luck. I didn\u2019t even check out I just walked out after my session because I did not want to deal with either of these rude females!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQ3dmNXal9BRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xfbee1c1f4e712354!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgID7vcWj_AE%7C%7C?hl=en",
